Detailed Description

Implement an iterator over a sonar cone.

this class implements an iterator which enumerates all cells of a grid-based map covered by a sonar cone originating at a given cell and looking in a given direction. Cells are enumerated from the sonar sensor on, progressing towaerds the scan limit of the sensor. While strictly increasing cell to origin distances for consecutively returned cells can not be guaranteed, cells are returned in mostly increasing distance order.

Construct a sonar cone iterator.

This constructor makes a sonar cone iterator for a sonar sensor located at position (x, y) in the map and looking into direction dir width a cone width of width and a maximum sensing range of len.

the direction dir is measured in radians against the x axis of the maps coordinate system. The scan range len is measured in units of cells, i.i cell edge length.

Parameters
xx coordinate of sensor position.
yy coordinate of sensor position.
dirorientation of sensor, i.e. direction of center beam.
widthsonar cone opening angle in radians.
lenmaximum sensing distance of the sonar sensor.

bool mapstore::MapStoreCone::nextCell ( int &  x,
int &  y 
)

Compute next cell in cone.

This function computes the next cell in the sonar cone, based on internal state. It is guaranteered that every cell covered by the sonar cone is returned exactly once.

The next cell's coordinates are returned in the supplied variables x and y. The return value of this function indicates if more cells are available (if return value is true) or if all cells covered by the cone have been returned (return value is false). No assumptions should be made regarding the order in which the cells are returned.

Example:

MapStore map(size_X, size_Y);
MapStoreCone msc(sensor_x, sensor_y, sensor_orient);
int x=0, y=0;
while (msc.nextCell(x,y)) {
// do something with the cell
double mapVal = map.get(x,y);
}
Parameters
x[out] x coordinate of next cell in the cone. The cells are enumerated by an internal state. No assumptions should be made regarding the order in which the cells are returned.
y[out] y coordinate of next cell in the cone. The cells are enumerated by an internal state. No assumptions should be made regarding the order in which the cells are returned.
Returns
flag if more cells are to be returned. If false, all cells in the cone have been returned.
